OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FBlustery
OL,6,Fshowers becoming more frequent this
OL,7,Fevening and overnight, heavy at times
OL,8,Fwith the risk of hail mixed in. Rather
OL,9,Fchilly, but the brisk northerly wind
OL,10,Fand cloud preventing a frost.
OL,11,
OL,12,CThursday:FScattered, blustery showers
OL,13,Fcontinue with some with hail and
OL,14,Fthunder possible. Gusty winds but
OL,15,Flighter in the east compared to
OL,16,FWednesday. Temperatures remaining
OL,17,Fbelow average for mid-May.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
